Seems like they're moving the melee classes closer to that baseline.  Verant calls warriors the &quot;Masters of Combat&quot;, yet it seems there's little to differentiate us except for having higher HP and AC.  Oh yeah, we're more resistant to magic.<br><br>Verant should explain the warrior class as being the &quot;Masters of getting hit&quot;, since our offensive skills are no better than other melee classes.  Now, more melee classes are gaining the same defensive skill caps as warriors, meaning they become better at doing the one thing we do best.  I hope this is just the start of the class balancing mods.<br><br>Sorry Edeina, this rant should probably go on the NAG board.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/5/01 12:59:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lookie lookie</span><hr size=1> Don't worry, Kleg. Not that I think you was worried, but still. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Many threads and posts fits nicely in either of the two folders. There will always be interesting and well grounded discussions in both, and they are very similar although General leans a bit more to serious announcements and questions, while NAG leans a bit more to rants and chit-chat. In many ways the main reason to have it split into two forums is to prevent it from clogging up too fast. Some people check the boards only weekly or so.<br><br>You are right that rants should primarily go to to NAG, but of course there is room for quite a bit of ranting on General as well. Besides, I don't consider your post a rant at all, more like a well grounded and well presented opinion.<br><br>And I'm afraid you are right. We might be about to return to the old ways where Warriors are the poor ones because hybrids can do all the warriors can do and a lot of other stuff on top of that. But I don't think we have to start worrying just yet. You have higher AC and HP then anyone else, no other class have as high offense AND defense, and you have those wonderful diciplines.<br><br>I think these changes are great, making the hybrids more viable again without making the warriors obsolete. But Verant will have to look out for their warriors now, if they continue too far in this direction... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :| --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/indifferent.gif ALT=":|"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p>Love, Edeina<br>Highelf Conjurer of Erollisi<br>Ayonae Ro Server<br><a href="http://Ayonae.Ro">Ayonae.Ro</a> Server Community Board</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufandariella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandariella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/5/01 2:50:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lookie lookie</span><hr size=1> bah, nothing for enchanters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Have you read the enchanter thread? LOL, enchanters are crazy. Man, they want Illusion: Face, so we can change face! Very useful <!--