 Lookie lookie</span><hr size=1> i agree completely Jzonn.<br><br>that´s about the same as this "druids and shamans get better heals, bash them now" thing, clerics will always be better at healing, and they will always be prefered for this reason, so there´s nothing wrong about giving the other two priest classes better healing abilities to better fill in the cleric´s role if a cleric is not available. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/5/01 5:13:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lookie lookie</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the kind words, Edeina...where should I mail the check?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>It's not that I mind the changes being made to hybrids.  They will ultimately benefit everyone in a group, and I'm happy for them.  I truly enjoy playing my warrior, although it would be nice if certain stats like AGI actually meant something significant.  I fell into the trap of making my AGI high instead of STR, thinking as a Halfling, I'll get hit less because I'm small and quick.  I'm regretting that decision now since I've learned AGI after 100 is essentially meaningless.<br><br>My thoughts came after reading through the warrior balancing threads, in which a lot of people were asking that warriors be made different than other classes.  Higher AC and moderately more HP are good things, and we can definitely absorb damage, but I think quite a few warriors would like to see more separation in combat skills in relation to hybrids, instead of less.<br><br>Warriors rely on equipment to differentiate themselves from other classes, but with the scarcity of cobalt and hard to obtain weapons, many warriors are outdamaged by monks, rangers, and shadowknights.  This has never been VI's intention, as they feel warrior damage should be second to that of a rogue.  Hell, I'm still wearing mostly crafted armor.  Crafted at level 52!!!!  With Kunark / Velious armor, hybrid classes can come very close if not exceed the AC of a warrior with only 1 or 2 pieces of new armor.  I can only hope the PoG offers me a chance to upgrade my AC.<br><br>Ughhhh.....I'll stop now as I'm beginning to ramble.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umorchaint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morchaint</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/5/01 6:03:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lookie lookie</span><hr size=1> Fanda, I am convinced that the illusion: face movement was started by those people who didn't know you could pick a face when they created their character, and got stuck with one they didn't like. :P<br><br>In any case, it's good to see that people aren't getting *too* worked up about these changes...remember they're still on Test.<br><br>Morchaint Poisonblade <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubelzebuth666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belzebuth666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/5/01 6:54:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard